### How to Use This Table

If you are using a **[diamond price calculator](https://diamondcritics.com/diamond-price-calculator/)**, you will notice that jumping from a "G" to an "E" can cost you thousands. By using this matrix, you are effectively "gaming" the system. You aren't buying a lower-quality stone; you are buying a stone that is technically optimized for its final environment.

For example, if you've decided on a yellow gold vintage-style setting, buying a D-color diamond is a waste of capital. The yellow prongs will make the diamond look warmer regardless.

You are much better off buying a **J-color** stone and putting those savings into a **[Super-Ideal Cut](https://diamondcritics.com/diamond-cut-guide/)**.

> 
